Greeting Greenfield families and happy new school year. The Greenfield Family Resource Center (GFRC) is happy to welcome everyone to the new school year and we all hope your first day back yesterday was great.

We realize that our school year may look a little different this year, but rest assured that the GFRC is here to support our community in any way we can.

Due to COVID19 restrictions, we understand that we may not always be able to accommodate in person assistance. However, we will be moving over many of our services here to our Facebook page and though our other social media channels. Stay tuned for more information about our live streams, updates and chances for prize giveaways :).

Please contact us @ 661-837-3720 should you have any questions or would like to make an appointment with us.

Be safe and healthy :).

Greetings Greenfield Community,

The staff at the Greenfield Family Resource Center wishes you all the best.

The California Parent and Youth Helpline provides support and resource referrals to parent and youth during the current COVID-19 pandemic, 7-days a week from 8:00 a.m. to 8:00 p.m. Call or text 1-855-4APARENT (855-427-2736) for services in English, Spanish and other languages.

For more information, please visit: https://caparentyouthhelpline.org/

Always remember that you can also contact the Greenfield Family Resource Center for assistance @ 661-837-3720.

Greetings Greenfield community. All the staff at the Greenfield Family Resource Center hopes you are doing well this fine Tuesday, morning.

We are reopening our doors to better serve the Greenfield community. Beginning Tuesday May 5th, Our office will be open from 9:00 AM to 12:00 PM Monday through Thursday. We will be closed on Fridays.

Also, due to COVID19 safety regulations, we ask all visitors that come to our office abide by our new health regulations to maintain wellness for other community members and our office staff.

If you are in need of assistance, please contact us at our number, 661-837-3720 or you can email Maricela Ortiz at ortizma@gfusd.net.

Be safe and have a great day :).

Happy Monday Greenfield! The Greenfield Family Resource Center is partnering with Smileland Dental to put on an art contest featuring the Smile Avengers!

To enter, you must be between 5-12 years of age and draw an original Super Hero to join the Smile Avengers. Simply fill out the entry form, it comes in both English and Spanish, and return the form to your nearest Smileland Dental Office.

The 1st place winner's character will be featured with the other Smile Avengers and receive 4 tickets to Disneyland!

The contest runs from now till November 15th. Don't miss your chance to enter :).

If you have any questions, you can contact Smileland Dental at (800) 400-3333 or the Greenfield Family Resource Center at (661)-837-3720.

Best of luck!!!

post_text:
Hello, and welcome to the 2019-2020 school year in the Greenfield Union School District.

I am excited to once again introduce the Greenfield Family Resource Center. With a legacy spanning over 20 years, the Greenfield Family Resource Center (GFRC) is a caring, compassionate, supportive facility where every member of the community is welcomed. The GFRC partners with the Greenfield Union School District, community organizations and agencies to help families be successful by strengthening children, parents, youth, and the community as a whole.

The Family Resource Center is ready to support every family. If you are interested in our many programs and services, please give us a call at 661-837-3720.

Come back to our Facebook page regularly to get updates on all our services, programs and upcoming events.

We look forward to hearing from you.

Have a great day!

Jordan Green
FRC Supervisor

post_text:
The Tell Me A Story School Readiness Program provides early childhood education (ages 0-5) to prepare young students for school success. Our goal is to have all children be prepared and confident for their future education. Parents learn alongside their students and are introduced to key concepts that encourage student success.

Please consider joining our program if you have a children ages 0-5. We will provide you with an enriching experience for both you as a parent and for your future student(s). We are currently taking registrations for our fall session. Give us a call to register as space is limited.

Look for our banners and flyers in the Greenfield area for more information.

To register for our program, please contact the Greenfield Family Resource Center at 661-837-3720.

Our program is supported by First 5 Kern & sponsored by the Greenfield Union School District.

#GUSD, #SchoolReadiness, #First5Kern, #Greenfield, #TMAS, #GreenfieldFamilyResourceCenter

Our Greenfield Family Resource Center Nutrition Program was hard at work this summer by hosting two Summer Cooking Camps and Summer Nutrition Education Challenges!

Our staff offered fun nutrition education lessons and food recipes for students. Students learned the joy of healthy eating and won some awesome prizes along the way. Students also got to tour a school kitchen and learned what it takes to feed so many students in our district.

A big thank you to our GFRC Nutrition Coordinator Nora Ortiz and Nutrtion Educator Juan Valencia. You both did an amazing job. A special shout out goes to Josh Rogers, our Director of Nutriton Services.

Our program would not be possible without the support of the Greenfield Union School District (GUSD), The GUSD Nutrition Department, and our donors. THANK YOU SO MUCH!!

If you are interested in participating in activities like these, please contact Nora Ortiz at the Greenfield Family Resource Center at 661-837-3720.

During our event we had presentations on nutrition, an awesome zumba exercise, and we cleaned up Greenfield Park by picking up trash and cigarettes, right behind McKee Middle School!

We had a great time and we hope to see you next year!

Don't forget to keep up with all the amazing events put on by the GFRC. We'll see you on Thursday, April 4th for our GFRC Health & Safety Fair!

#HealthandSafety, #Community, #Greenfield, #GreenfieldUnionSchoolDistrict, #GFRC, #FamilyResources, #GFUSD #McKeeMiddleSchool

The Greenfield Family Resource Center's Summer Bridge Program is almost here!

This 4 week program will be offered during the months of April-May and will prepare children entering Kindergarten in the fall. Our goal is to have children feel secure, prepared and confident for their future.

Students will gain the necessary skills to transition into Kindergarten, while providing a safe and nurturing environment to learn and grow. Come join us for music, games and fun for you and your future kindgartener :).

To sign up for this amazing program, please contact the Greenfield Family Resource Center at 661-837-3720.

We hope to see you there :).

post_text:
Nurturing Parenting: Live In Harmony and Have Fun Together

FREE Parenting Classes for Families with Children Ages 0-5

COME AND DEVELOP YOUR UNDERSTANDING, KNOWLEDGE AND SKILLS AND LEARN ABOUT PRACTICES AND STRATEGIES OF NURTURING PARENTING. THE INFORMATION OBTAINED IN THESE CLASSES WILL BE BENEFICIAL TO YOUR FAMILY.

Topics include:
 Developmental Stages
 Getting Needs Met
 Discipline vs. Punishment
 Setting Limits
 Verbal and Physical Redirection/ Praise
 Family Values, Morals, and Rules
 Positive Ways To Deal with Stress and Anger

FOR INFORMATION AND REGISTRATION CONTACT:
NELIA RAMOS
GREENFIELD FAMILY RESOURCE CENTER 5400 MONITOR ST. BAKERSFIELD, CA 93307 661-837-3720

https://www.facebook.com/greenfieldfrc

FAMILIES CAN APPLY FOR COVERED CALIFORNIA, MEDI-CAL, AND CAL-FRESH AT OUR OFFICE.
